# Breakout Recreation in Godot

## Overview

This project is a free, open-source recreation of the classic Breakout game, implemented using the Godot game engine. It serves as a learning project for those interested in game development with Godot.

## Features

- Classic Breakout gameplay
- Ball physics and paddle control
- Destructible blocks
- Score tracking (Not yet implemented)
- Game over and win conditions

## Running the Game

- Visit the releases to download the game executable pack

## Modifying the Game

### Prerequisites

- Godot Engine 4.x (download from [Godot's official website](https://godotengine.org/))

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/himea-saito/Breakout.git
   ```
2. Open Godot Engine
3. Click "Import"
4. Navigate to the cloned repository folder and select the `project.godot` file
5. Click "Import & Edit"


## How to Play

- Use the left and right arrow keys (or A and D) to aim your launch or move the paddle
- Press spacebar to launch the ball
- Bounce the ball off the paddle to break the blocks
- Break all blocks to win
- Don't let the ball fall below the paddle!

## Project Structure

- `scenes/`: Contains all game scenes
- `scripts/`: Contains all GDScript files
- `assets/`: Contains graphics, sounds, and other resources

